The paper deals with privacy protection in pervasive computing environments, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed scheme involves clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in data mining and machine learning (cs.DS). The scheme also involves dividing the area into clusters, which is a technique used in spatial databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses privacy analysis and complexity analysis, which are topics in machine learning and algorithms (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.SI), respectively.
